<br>
Damage bonuses start at around L27-28, not L50, and nowadays they are correctly listed on the weapons for <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> your level</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> when you inspect the weapon.  If 2 people of significantly different levels put a weapon in the trade window, they will see different bonuses when they inspect it.  <br>
<br>
The bonus is applied *every hit* with the weapon in main hand, and are a purely static added piece (and the &quot;ripostes get no damage bonus&quot; thing is also incorrect.  You do indeed get bonuses on ripostes).  <br>
<br>
Your minimum hit is not JUST the bonus, but :<br>
(weapon damage/10) + bonus <br>
(rounding the first part to the nearest integer).  Damage bonuses do not apply to offhand, just main hand (and 2handers).<br>
<br>
I have never ever ever hit for less than (bonus + damage/10) with main hand or a 2hander or for less than (damage/10) with offhand, except on monsters with a rune that's wearing off.  Bear in mind some mobs such as NPC shadowknights which aren't usually thought of as &quot;rune casters&quot; do buff themselves with shieldskin. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=lythe>Lythe</A> at: 9/20/02 9:36:50 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uthedrunkenmage.showPublicProfile?language=EN>The Drunken Mage</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 86<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/20/02 9:45:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3943.topic&index=14>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_die.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Um</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> I could be wrong on this, but I think the dmg bonus you see on the weapon stats is what it would be at level 60<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
The damage bonus displayed on a weapon that is in your inventory or that you have equipped is the damage bonus that YOU will get with the weapon.<br>
<br>
If I have a 1hs in my inventory and look at it, I'll see a damage bonus of 11.  If I hand it to a level 50 warrior, he will see a different bonus (I forget what the bonus was at 50).<br>
<br>
I'm not sure how this works with the new linking that you can do... not sure if it shows the bonus appropriate to the person who made the link, or the person who is viewing the link.. never thought to test that.<br>
